// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Clue - AccessTerminalGranted 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Clue Name :
"P3229744399" "Access Code: Terminus"
// DetailString :
"P1527724401" "You've coerced the Chief Temporal Scientist into giving you root permissions to the Access Terminals used to interface with the Time Matrix.  With this code in hand, you should now be able to use the Matrix Keys given to you by your future self."

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Dialog - PrimaryTerminal 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Page Intro Text :
"P1847845894" "<color orange>This is one of the Time Matrix access terminals.  The designation in bold letters displays the word - Primary.</color><br><br><color BurlyWood>TIME MATRIX ACCESS TERMINAL ALPHA.<br><br>ROOT ACCESS PRIVILEGES INITIATED.<br><br>ENTER MATRIX ALGORITHM."
// Answer Text :
"P3529339040" "Enter algorithm from the Matrix Key."
// Answer Text :
"P4085482278" "SHUT DOWN"
// Page InformationPage1 Text :
"P3304205001" "<color BurlyWood>ALGORITHM ACCEPTED<br><br>Initiating Time Sequence: 7,300 revolutions.<br><br>SEQUENCE COMPLETED.  ALL URANIUM DEPLETED - INITIATING SHUTDOWN."

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Dialog - SecondaryTerminal 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Page Intro Text :
"P2980583604" "<color orange>This is one of the Time Matrix access terminals.  The designation in bold letters displays the word - Secondary.</color><br><br><color BurlyWood>TIME MATRIX ACCESS TERMINAL BETA.<br><br>ROOT ACCESS PRIVILEGES INITIATED.<br><br>ENTER MATRIX ALGORITHM."
// Answer Text :
"P761127670" "Enter another algorithm from the Matrix Key."
// Page InformationPage1 Text :
"P273062304" "<color BurlyWood>ALGORITHM ACCEPTED<br><br>Initiating Time Sequence: 109,500 revolutions.<br><br>SEQUENCE COMPLETED.  ALL URANIUM DEPLETED - INITIATING SHUTDOWN."

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Dialog - TertiaryTerminal 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Page Intro Text :
"P2678418936" "<color orange>This is one of the Time Matrix access terminals.  The designation in bold letters displays the word - Tertiary.</color><br><br><color BurlyWood>TIME MATRIX ACCESS TERMINAL OMEGA.<br><br>ROOT ACCESS PRIVILEGES INITIATED.<br><br>ENTER MATRIX ALGORITHM."
// Page InformationPage1 Text :
"P1190084756" "<color BurlyWood>ALGORITHM ACCEPTED<br><br>Initiating Time Sequence: 3,650,000 revolutions.<br><br>SEQUENCE COMPLETED.  ALL URANIUM DEPLETED - INITIATING SHUTDOWN."

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Dialog - FutureSelf 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Page Intro Text :
"P237713835" "How is this possible?  It's like I'm looking into the mirror, yet I'm so young.<br><br>Explain yourself at once or I will snuff out your pitiful excuse for a life."
// Answer Text :
"P2961665261" "You contacted me from the future.  I'm you from the past!"
// Page InformationPage1 Text :
"P559027444" "What?!  That is the most ridiculous thing I've ever heard.  Aha...<br><br>This is some foolish trick Frostfire has come up with, isn't it?"
// Answer Text :
"P3356027995" "Frostfire?  What does he have to do with anything?"
// Page InformationPage2 Text :
"P4188935155" "Do you expect me to believe that you're me from the past, but yet you don't seem to know Frostfire is the bane of my - our - very existence?<br><br>He is there to foil my every step!  Even now, as my minions complete the serum I have spent decades perfecting, Frostfire and his hero sidekicks are battering down the doors to my base.<br><br>And you!  You interrupt me at my moment of triumph?!"
// Answer Text :
"P3705974057" "You told me there was a critical mistake in our master plan."
// Page InformationPage3 Text :
"P3195450372" "Mistake?!  I do NOT make mistakes, cretin!  My immortality serum is PERFECT!  How DARE YOU speak to me this way, insect!<br><br>Now it is time for you to --"
// Answer Text :
"P3720851344" "Continue"
// Page InformationPage4 Text :
"P3345005560" "<color orange>You hear a loud zapping sound coming from the direction of where the Primary Terminal was housed.</color>"
// Answer Text :
"P3898145311" "Close"

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Dialog - FarFutureSelf 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Page Intro Text :
"P3631321403" "It sickens me to look at you - at what I once was.  How is it possible that I - the most powerful being upon this world - came from this pitiful embryonic cluster of snot and pus that stands before me?"
// Answer Text :
"P3883384741" "YOU DARE SPEAK TO ME TH--"
// Page InformationPage1 Text :
"P2632746152" "<color orange>With a flick of the wrist, your future self fills you with the most excruciating pain you have ever felt in your existence.  Another flick and it's over.</color><br><br>Were anyone else within my empire to speak out of turn as you just did, well, I would pull out their skeleton through their mouth - and then let them die weeks later.  However, I do not know what would happen were I to kill my own self in the past.<br><br>You are pitiful because you could not stop Frostfire all those centuries ago.  And now, he is all that stands in my way of global domination!  ALL BECAUSE OF YOUR SIMPERING, PATHETIC WEAKNESS!"
// Answer Text :
"P209159956" "Frostfire?! Is this why you contacted me?  To tell me about Frostfire?!"
// Page InformationPage2 Text :
"P3560414945" "SILENCE!  Your ignorance knows no bounds!  Frostfire was there when I drank deeply from that mysterious well in the former continent of Europe!  He, too, acquired the limitless power I now possess.  BECAUSE OF YOU!<br><br>Had you stopped him, he would not have supped from that ambrosia of the gods!  I have exterminated all those upon the planet who dare to show an inkling of power, yet HE STILL MOCKS ME!<br><br>But his time has now come.  I will finally be rid of this thorn in my side."
// Answer Text :
"P366112588" "Was that the mistake you wanted to warn me about?"
// Page InformationPage3 Text :
"P873950642" "I CARE NOTHING FOR THE QUESTIONING OF AN IGNORAMUS THE LIKES OF YOU!  I have no desire to 'warn' you of anything.  You failed.  And now, centuries later, I shall be the one to correct the mistakes of my past - mistakes such as you.<br><br>Even now, as I listen to your incessant prattling, my dear friend Frostfire is feeling his power ebbing away.  Even he can not withstand the soul-draining effects of Nethermatter.<br><br>This is where our conversation ends, my shame.  I now depart to finish off my lifelong nemes--"
// Page InformationPage4 Text :
"P766923366" "<color orange>You hear a loud zapping sound coming from the direction of where the Secondary Terminal was housed.</color>"

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Dialog - UltimateSelf 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Page Intro Text :
"P2114993534" "Ah... It is good to look upon a person again after all these millennia, even if it is only myself from the past.<br><br>I knew you would be able to find me."
// Answer Text :
"P2283969752" "You were the one who contacted me, weren't you?"
// Page InformationPage1 Text :
"P4211262120" "Yes, it was I.  I am you from thousands of years in the future.  Or rather, you're me from thousands of years in the past.  It required the power of a god to break the timestream to get you this message, and a god I am."
// Answer Text :
"P65625632" "You mean... I'm a god in the future?"
// Page InformationPage2 Text :
"P2775263389" "Not 'a' god.  The only god.  And this is why I need to warn you of the greatest mistake I made - you will make.<br><br>We stole the power of the gods forever ago - or many years in your future, from your point of view.  A man named Frostfire was there in the chamber, pleading for me - us - to not drink from source of the gods.  He was standing in front of that well as he begged for me not to go through with it.  I could have pushed him in and taken all the power for myself, but in my hubris I chose to taunt him instead.  For just a few moments, the same amount of time it took to insult my former foe, I could have prevented the greatest failure I have ever performed.<br><br>But with this knowledge I give you, YOU CAN CHANGE THE FUTURE!"
// Answer Text :
"P1025803032" "So you're saying that I should push him into the well when I have the chance?"
// Page InformationPage3 Text :
"P628766744" ""No!  You don't understand!  That power was meant for him!  Not me!  He drew from the well, but only half of it.  It wasn't enough to stop me from killing him with Nethermatter.<br><br> The Nethermatter was as dangerous to me as it was to him, for we each possessed only one half of the power of the gods.  If he would have had all the power, he would have been invulnerable to the Nethermatter.  Perhaps he would have been powerful enough to even create life itself!"
// Answer Text :
"P2234331381" "Hold on... with *all* the power one could create life!?"
// Page InformationPage4 Text :
"P40246484" "Yes.  It was the source of creation.  However...<br><br>Had I listened to him instead of insulting him - had I turned away from my deadly course - had I understood that my path only led to destruction...<br><br>Then he would have taken all that power unto himself... and used it to turn the world into a paradise Man has only ever been able to dream of.<br><br>But instead I used that power to ERADICATE all life on the planet.<br><br>All life in the galaxy.<br><br>And yet I still live.  All alone.  For the rest of Eternity."
// Answer Text :
"P3268951864" "I see.  So... I have the chance to change the future?"
// Page InformationPage5 Text :
"P274955053" "Yes!  And that is why I speak to you now.  You can change that one moment in your near future.  You can do what is right.<br><br>Why are you looking at me that way?  Your eyes... they burn in a way mine did when..."
// Answer Text :
"P139883752" "When we learn from our REAL mistakes?"
// Page InformationPage6 Text :
"P253504350" "No... No, you musn't!  You must give the power to Frostfire or we're doomed!"
// Answer Text :
"P1019187006" "Actually... You're the one who's doomed.  *I'm* going to be a full god!"

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Task Header Items 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// IntroString :
"P1784430787" "You continue listening to the message sent by your future self.<br><br>'Crey Industries has a secret lab that they are using to conduct experiments on the time-space continuum.  I found it many centuries ago, and this is where I - you - would begin forming your - my - master plan.  Within the lab are three matrices they're using to open rifts in time.  Encoded in this message are three keycodes that will locate me - you - in the past - er - in your future.<br><br>You MUST know what you did wrong or EVERYTHING will be ruined!"
// AcceptString :
"P1817151690" "Speak to your future self to learn of your master plan!"
// SendOffString :
"P4114332945" "Within the message projection device is the location of where your destiny lies.  Go seek it out while you still have... time!"
// ActiveTaskString :
"P2656881974" "Speak to your future self!"
// YoureStillBusyString :
"P246134511" "You still have a date with destiny.  Find the Crey lab and use the keycode on the Time Matrix... then speak to yourself from the future!"
// TaskTitle :
"P3426864100" "<font face=title><scale 1.1><span align=center><color orange>My Other Selves</color></span></scale></font>"
// TaskSubTitle :
"P2880686022" "<span align=center><color orange><i>Villain Morality Mission</i></color></span>"

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// MissionDef 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// EntryString :
"P3930796106" "This place looks unfamiliar, but you have a very odd sense of deja vu as you look around the place.  You're sure that Crey has this place locked up tight, so you'll need to find someone in charge to give you access to their computers.  Hopefully they'll put up a fight first."
// ExitStringSuccess :
"P3909206538" "<font face=title><scale 1.1><span align=center><color orange>My Other Selves</color></span></scale></font><br><span align=center><color red><i>Morality Mission</i></color></span><br><br>You - from thousands of years in the future -  attempted to sway you towards the pathetic and pitiful path of righteousness.<br><br>Instead, you learned how to become a being of untold power one day.  And you can make sure this happens with nothing more than one short, swift kick to the face.<br><br>In time, your master plan will be fully realized.  In time."

